@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"
@TOC "Main"

Offset is a little utility for programmers to calculate the offset of
a field from any OS 3.1 structure, the size of the structure or what field
there is at a certain offset. For example:

offset gadget.width          @{B}Output:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}8@{FG TEXT}

offset gadget.8              @{B}Output:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}Width@{FG TEXT}

offset gadget                @{B}Output:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}44@{FG TEXT}

offset gadget.$1e            @{B}Output:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}MutualExclude@{FG TEXT}

offset gadget.0x1A           @{B}Output:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}GadgetText@{FG TEXT}

There are some additional options available. See @{" Usage " LINK "Usage"}
@ENDNODE

