@NODE "Installation" "Installation"
@TOC "Main"

Use the supplied installation script to install Offset!!! If you do not then
watch out:

Offset usually needs to have it's comment (fib_Comment) set to the path of
"Structure.Offsets", i.e. the file containing the information about the OS
3.1 structures. I say usually because if Offset can't retrieve the path from
the comment it will still try to load the file from (in this order):

	"Structure.Offsets"
	"PROGDIR:Structure.Offsets"
	"S:Structure.Offsets"
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Usage" "Usage"
@TOC "Main"

Offset can actually be used only from a Shell:

The argument template of Offset is:

                 @{FG SHINE}NAME/A,SHOWHEX/S,SHOWSIZE/S,SHOWWINDOW/S@{FG TEXT}

@{FG SHINE}___________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯

@{FG SHINE}NAME@{FG TEXT}        Depends on what information you want to get. To get the size of
            a structure specify only it's name. For example:

		@{BG SHINE}1.@{BG FILL}@{FG SHINE}Boot:C@{BG SHINE}@{FG TEXT}>@{BG BACKGROUND} offset Window
	        136

		@{BG SHINE}1.@{BG FILL}@{FG SHINE}Boot:C@{BG SHINE}@{FG TEXT}>@{BG BACKGROUND} offset Window SHOWHEX
	        136 0x0088

	    To get the offset of a structure field specify both the struc-
	    ture name and the field name, separated by '@{FG SHINE}.@{FG TEXT}', '@{FG SHINE}->@{FG TEXT}' or '@{FG SHINE}^.@{FG TEXT}'.
	    For example:
	    
		@{BG SHINE}1.@{BG FILL}@{FG SHINE}Boot:C@{BG SHINE}@{FG TEXT}>@{BG BACKGROUND} offset Window.Title
		32

		@{BG SHINE}1.@{BG FILL}@{FG SHINE}Boot:C@{BG SHINE}@{FG TEXT}>@{BG BACKGROUND} offset Window->Title
		32

		@{BG SHINE}1.@{BG FILL}@{FG SHINE}Boot:C@{BG SHINE}@{FG TEXT}>@{BG BACKGROUND} offset Window^.Title
		32

		@{BG SHINE}1.@{BG FILL}@{FG SHINE}Boot:C@{BG SHINE}@{FG TEXT}>@{BG BACKGROUND} offset Window.Title SHOWHEX
		32 0x0020

	    To find out what field there is at a certain structure offset,
	    you must specify both the structure name and the offset, again
	    separated by '@{FG SHINE}.@{FG TEXT}', '@{FG SHINE}->@{FG TEXT}' or '@{FG SHINE}^.@{FG TEXT}'. The offset must be specified
	    either in decimal or hex format. For example:
	    
		@{BG SHINE}1.@{BG FILL}@{FG SHINE}Boot:C@{BG SHINE}@{FG TEXT}>@{BG BACKGROUND} offset Screen.14
		Title

	    	@{BG SHINE}1.@{BG FILL}@{FG SHINE}Boot:C@{BG SHINE}@{FG TEXT}>@{BG BACKGROUND} offset Screen.0xE
	    	Title

		@{BG SHINE}1.@{BG FILL}@{FG SHINE}Boot:C@{BG SHINE}@{FG TEXT}>@{BG BACKGROUND} offset Screen.$E
		Title

	    Note that some structures have more fields at the same offset
	    (unions). Offset will output all of them, including the union
	    name. For example:
	    
	    	@{BG SHINE}1.@{BG FILL}@{FG SHINE}Boot:C@{BG SHINE}@{FG TEXT}>@{BG BACKGROUND} offset DosList.16
		dol_misc
		dol_misc.dol_handler
		dol_misc.dol_handler.dol_Handler
		dol_misc.dol_volume
		dol_misc.dol_volume.dol_VolumeDate
		dol_misc.dol_assign
		dol_misc.dol_assign.dol_AssignName


@{FG SHINE}SHOWHEX@{FG TEXT}     Print the result also in hex. The output will be:

		<DEC><@{FG FILL}SPACE@{FG TEXT}><HEX>

	    For example:

		@{BG SHINE}1.@{BG FILL}@{FG SHINE}Boot:C@{BG SHINE}@{FG TEXT}>@{BG BACKGROUND} offset Screen.Title SHOWHEX
		22 0x0016

	    This option does of course not affect the output if you were
	    asking for the field name of a structure's offset.


@{FG SHINE}SHOWSIZE@{FG TEXT}    Prints also the size of a field. If you were asking for the off-
	    set of a certain structure's field, the output will be either:

		[<FIELDSIZE>]<@{FG FILL}SPACE@{FG TEXT}><OFFSET>

	    or, if you have also specified SHOWHEX:

	    	[<FIELDSIZE>]<@{FG FILL}SPACE@{FG TEXT}><DEC-OFFSET><@{FG FILL}SPACE@{FG TEXT}><HEX-OFFSET>

	    If you were asking for the field name of a structure's offset,
	    the output will be:

		[<FIELDSIZE>]<@{FG FILL}SPACE@{FG TEXT}><FIELDNAME>

	    The width of <FIELDSIZE> is always three characters! Examples:

		@{BG SHINE}1.@{BG FILL}@{FG SHINE}Boot:C@{BG SHINE}@{FG TEXT}>@{BG BACKGROUND} offset Screen.Title SHOWSIZE
		[  4] 22

		@{BG SHINE}1.@{BG FILL}@{FG SHINE}Boot:C@{BG SHINE}@{FG TEXT}>@{BG BACKGROUND} offset Screen.Title SHOWSIZE SHOWHEX
		[  4] 22 0x0016

		@{BG SHINE}1.@{BG FILL}@{FG SHINE}Boot:C@{BG SHINE}@{FG TEXT}>@{BG BACKGROUND} offset Screen.22 SHOWSIZE
		[  4] Title


@{FG SHINE}SHOWWINDOW@{FG TEXT}  Instead of printing the result to the output window it will be
	    shown in a requester.
@ENDNODE

